      "created_at" : "Mon Oct 27 01:30:03 +0000 2025",
      "favorited" : false,
      "full_text" : "Therefore, the moral challenge is not to escape the false night, but to see through it, to allow the darkness to clarify what the light of imitation obscured. Authenticity emerges not by fleeing illusion, but by recognizing its ontological dependence.",
      "lang" : "en",
      "in_reply_to_screen_name" : "GeorgeW479744",
